MOst Noble King, Most Gracious <lb/>
<normalised orig="Soueraigne" auto="true">Sovereign</normalised>, as Daniel said to Darius, <lb/>
so say I to your high <normalised orig="Maiestie" auto="true">Majesty</normalised>, <quote type="biblical" ana="Dan 6.21">O King <lb/>
<normalised orig="liue" auto="true">live</normalised> for <normalised orig="euer" auto="true">ever</normalised></quote>. And this wishing, <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 9.1">I <lb/>
say the truth in Christ, I <normalised orig="lye" auto="true">lie</normalised> not</quote>: My <lb/>
hearts desire, and prayer to God for <lb/>
your <normalised orig="Maiestie" auto="true">Majesty</normalised> being not <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> that you may be <lb/>
<normalised orig="euerlastingly" auto="true">everlastingly</normalised> <normalised orig="saued" auto="true">saved</normalised> in the World to come, but that <lb/>
also in this World, and in these your Earthly <normalised orig="Kingdomes" auto="true">Kingdoms</normalised>, <lb/>
with the assurance of the <normalised orig="Kingdome" auto="true">Kingdom</normalised> of <lb/>
<normalised orig="Glorie" auto="true">Glory</normalised>, you may be <normalised orig="preuented" auto="true">prevented</normalised> with the blessings of <lb/>
<normalised orig="goodnesse" auto="true">goodness</normalised> belonging to this Life, and that the <lb/>
<normalised orig="Crowne" auto="true">Crown</normalised> of pure Gold, that God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> set <normalised orig="vpon" auto="true">upon</normalised> your <lb/>
<normalised orig="Royall" auto="true">Royal</normalised> Head, may there <normalised orig="remaine" auto="true">remain</normalised> accompanied with <lb/>
all Peace, <normalised orig="Prosperitie" auto="true">Prosperity</normalised>, and Honour, meet for a Prince <lb/>
of so great <normalised orig="Maiestie" auto="true">Majesty</normalised>, <normalised orig="maugre" auto="true">meagre</normalised> the Head of all your <lb/>
Enemies, Papists, and other <normalised orig="whatsoeuer" auto="true">whatsoever</normalised>. And now <lb/>
O Sacred King, as Paul <normalised orig="craued" auto="true">craved</normalised> King Agrippa his <lb/>
patience, for hearing of him, because he knew <lb/>
him to be expert in all the <normalised orig="customes" auto="true">customs</normalised> of the <normalised orig="Iewes" auto="true">Jews</normalised>, <lb/>
so <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> I most humbly <normalised orig="craue" auto="true">crave</normalised> your Princely grace, <lb/>
and <normalised orig="pacience" auto="true">patience</normalised>, for me to write a few Words <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> <lb/>
