the Body cannot be without the Head for <normalised orig="gouernement" auto="true">government</normalised> <lb/>
thereof, so the Head cannot be without the <lb/>
Body to support it: As one Member cannot say to <lb/>
another, I <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> no need of thee; so, and much <normalised orig="lesse" auto="true">less</normalised> <lb/>
can the Head and the Body so say to each other. In <lb/>
respect therefore that the Head <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> need of the <lb/>
Body, as well as the Body of the Head, I thought <lb/>
that the Petition of the whole Body would be <lb/>
